# Code owners -- routes review by zone (SWE-at-Google ch.10, "Ownership").
#
# An owner is the gatekeeper of a directory: GitHub auto-requests their review on
# any PR that touches it, and -- once branch protection requires review from code
# owners -- their approval gates the merge. Today adc_cpp is solo plus agents, so
# @wolf75222 owns every zone; the per-zone split is deliberate, not redundant. It
# documents the responsible owner per area and prepares reviewer auto-assignment for when
# the team grows (adding a second owner to a line is then a one-line change).
#
# This file only declares ownership. Turning it into a merge gate is the branch
# protection decision (ADC-166): enable "Require review from Code Owners" on master.
# Until then CODEOWNERS drives review auto-assignment, not enforcement.
#
# Matching: last matching pattern wins, so the global fallback comes first and the
# specific zones override it. See CONTRIBUTING.md "Code review".

# Global fallback -- any path not matched by a zone below.
*                       @wolf75222

# C++23 core: mesh, AMR, numerics, elliptic, coupling, runtime, physics, validation.
/include/adc/           @wolf75222

# Python bindings, the DSL surface and the Python tests.
/python/                @wolf75222

# C++ tests, benchmarks and fuzzing harnesses.
/tests/                 @wolf75222
/bench/                 @wolf75222
/fuzz/                  @wolf75222

# Build, packaging, CI/CD and developer tooling.
/CMakeLists.txt         @wolf75222
/CMakePresets.json      @wolf75222
/cmake/                 @wolf75222
/.github/               @wolf75222
/scripts/               @wolf75222

# Documentation (Sphinx site, vendored guides, doc tooling).
/docs/                  @wolf75222
